{"id":1698895,"retrievedAt":"2026-05-20T13:57:37.880Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[],"homepage":"","id":1698895,"imdb_id":"tt5285234","origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"The Man Who Disappeared","overview":"In 1937, having just returned from Mexico, and a failure on the stage, playwright and theater director Antonin Artaud embarked for Ireland on another mythical journey. Though finally cured of his lifelong drug addiction, he was nevertheless broke, alone, and unable to speak English. Lotringer’s film is a gripping docufiction about this period in Artaud’s life, focusing in particular on the ten days he spent on the stark Aran Islands before he became delirious and was sent back to France in a straightjacket. THE MAN WHO DISAPPEARED was shot on location on the spectacular Island of Inishmore from 2014-15.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/3nBweLJXT0Ir2erLpYYql8BU6nK.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2015-10-15","revenue":0,"runtime":49,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"The Man Who Disappeared","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"external_ids":{"imdb_id":"tt5285234","wikidata_id":null,"facebook_id":null,"instagram_id":null,"twitter_id":null},"images":{"backdrops":[],"logos":[],"posters":[{"aspect_ratio":0.666,"height":941,"iso_3166_1":null,"iso_639_1":null,"file_path":"/3nBweLJXT0Ir2erLpYYql8BU6nK.jpg","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"width":627},{"aspect_ratio":0.666,"height":941,"iso_3166_1":null,"iso_639_1":null,"file_path":"/rqsXbx60U94hDwCUSw4NFk7Ouj0.jpg","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"width":627}]},"keywords":{"keywords":[]},"release_dates":{"results":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","release_dates":[{"certification":"","descriptors":[],"iso_639_1":"","note":"","release_date":"2015-10-15T00:00:00.000Z","type":3}]}]},"videos":{"results":[]},"cre